> <mn>4</mn> </mrow> </math>", "isCorrect": true, "image": null}], "correctValue": null, "solution": {"text": "<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/pyq/jee_advanced/f388598d-0252-482e-8fd8-e898914b8cb8-Screenshotfrom2020-08-0508-56-08.png\" style=\"width: 321px; height: 181px;\" />Field due to small sphere<br /><math> <mrow> <mo>=</mo> <mfrac> <mrow> <mtext>K</mtext> <msub> <mi>&#961;</mi> <mn>1</mn> </msub> <mfrac> <mrow> <mn>4</mn> </mrow> <mrow> <mn>3</mn> </mrow> </mfrac> <mi>&#960;</mi> <msup> <mtext>R</mtext> <mn>3</mn> </msup> </mrow> <mrow> <msup> <mrow> <mfenced close=\")\" open=\"(\" separators=\",\"> <mrow> <mn>2</mn> <mtext>R</mtext> </mrow> </mfenced> </mrow> <mn>2</mn> </msup> </mrow> </mfrac> </mrow> </math><br />Field due to bigger sphere<br /><math> <mrow> <mo>=</mo> <mfrac> <mrow> <mtext>K</mtext> <msub> <mi>&#961;</mi> <mn>2</mn> </msub> <mfrac> <mrow> <mn>4</mn> </mrow> <mrow> <mn>3</mn> </mrow> </mfrac> <mn>&#960;</mn> <msup> <mrow> <mfenced close=\")\" open=\"(\" separators=\",\"> <mrow> <mn>2</mn> <mtext>R</mtext> </mrow> </mfenced> </mrow> <mn>3</mn> </msup> <mo>&#215;</mo> <mtext>R</mtext> </mrow> <mrow> <msup> <mrow> <mfenced close=\")\" open=\"(\" separators=\",\"> <mrow> <mn>2</mn> <mtext>R</mtext> </mrow> </mfenced> </mrow> <mn>3</mn> </msup> </mrow> </mfrac> </mrow> </math><br />The net electric field at point&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi></math>&nbsp;will be</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mover><mi>E</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover><mi>net</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p><p>Equating above two, we get <math> <mrow> <mfrac> <mrow> <msub> <mi>&#961;</mi> <mn>1</mn> </msub> </mrow> <mrow> <msub> <mi>&#961;</mi> <mn>2</mn> </msub> </mrow> </mfrac> <mo>=</mo> <mn>4</mn> </mrow> </math><br />[Charges cannot be of an opposite sign otherwise field will not zero]<br /><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/pyq/jee_advanced/da6